            "id": "4561294",
            "title": "U.S. Antimony wins $27M government contract for critical minerals",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\"><span>United States Antimony (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UAMY\" title=\"United States Antimony Corporation\">UAMY</a></span>) +3.8% pre-market Thursday after saying it was <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20425564-united-states-antimony-corporation-selected-for-strategic-antimony-supply-chain-expansion\" target=\"_self\" title=\"awarded\">awarded</a> $27M by the U.S. Department of War under Title III of the Defense Production Act to boost domestic extraction, processing, and refinement of critical materials.</span></p>\n<p><span>The company said the investment will fund modernization and capacity expansion at its Montana facility to refine and produce antimony used in flame retardants, batteries, munitions, and defense applications, and support its initiative to establish domestic antimony excavation and extraction in Alaska.</span></p>\n<p><span>The award is one of three made by the DPA Purchases Office totaling $58.5M since the beginning of FY 2026, which were delayed by a government shutdown; US Antimony's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UAMY\" title=\"United States Antimony Corporation\">UAMY</a>) recipient cost share of the $27M award totals $3.9M.</span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
