            "id": "4561292",
            "title": "Strait of Hormuz closure looks like a coin flip as traders forecast essentially 50-50 chance",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Rising tensions between the United States and Iran are drawing renewed attention to the Strait of Hormuz, one of the world’s most strategically important energy corridors. Investors are increasingly focused on the risk of disruptions to the narrow waterway, which serves as a vital transit route for global oil supplies.</p>\n<p>Roughly 20 million barrels per day of petroleum liquids pass through the Strait of Hormuz, making it the world’s second-largest oil transit chokepoint. Any prolonged disruption could have significant implications for global energy markets and inflation. </p>\n<p>Market participants are closely watching the probability of such a scenario. On prediction market Kalshi, traders are currently pricing in roughly even odds that Iran could effectively close the Strait of Hormuz for at least seven days.</p>\n<p>See the probabilities forecasted below when asked:  Will Iran effectively close the Strait of Hormuz for 7+ days?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Before May of 2026 – 45% chance</li>\n<li>Before August of 2026 – 55% chance</li>\n<li>Before 2027 – 53% chance </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>S&amp;P 500 ETFs:</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPY\" title=\"State Street SPDR S&amp;P 500 ETF Trust\">SPY</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VOO\" title=\"Vanguard 500 Index Fund ETF\">VOO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IVV\" title=\"iShares Core S&amp;P 500 ETF\">IVV</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RSP\" title=\"Invesco S&amp;P 500 Eql Wght ETF\">RSP</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SSO\" title=\"ProShares Ultra S&amp;P500 ETF\">SSO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UPRO\" title=\"ProShares UltraPro S&amp;P500 ETF\">UPRO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SH\" title=\"ProShares Short S&amp;P500 ETF\">SH</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SDS\" title=\"ProShares UltraShort S&amp;P500 ETF\">SDS</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPXU\" title=\"ProShares UltraPro Short S&amp;P500 ETF\">SPXU</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXAIX\" title=\"Fidelity 500 Index Fund\">FXAIX</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VFIAX\" title=\"Vanguard 500 Index Fund Admiral\">VFIAX</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VFFSX\" title=\"Vanguard 500 Index Fund Institutional Select\">VFFSX</a></span></span>), and (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SWPPX\" title=\"Schwab S&amp;P 500 Index Fund\">SWPPX</a></span></span>).</p>\n<p><strong>Energy ETFs:</strong> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XLE\" title=\"State Street Energy Select Sector SPDR ETF\">XLE</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMLP\" title=\"Alerian MLP ETF\">AMLP</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VDE\" title=\"Vanguard Energy Index Fund ETF\">VDE</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/XOP\" title=\"State Street SPDR S&amp;P Oil &amp; Gas Expl &amp; Prod ETF\">XOP</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OIH\" title=\"VanEck Oil Services ETF\">OIH</a></span></span>), and (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IXC\" title=\"iShares Global Energy ETF\">IXC</a></span></span>). </p>\n<p><strong>Oil ETFs: </strong>(<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USO\" title=\"United States Oil Fund LP ETF\">USO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UCO\" title=\"ProShares Ultra Bloomberg Crude Oil ETF\">UCO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DBO\" title=\"Invesco DB Oil Fund ETF\">DBO</a></span></span>), (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OILK\" title=\"ProShares K-1 Free Crude Oil ETF\">OILK</a></span></span>), and (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USL\" title=\"United States 12 Month Oil Fund LP ETF\">USL</a></span></span>). Natural Gas ETFs: (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol