            "id": "4561263",
            "title": "Six Flags Entertainment shedding seven parks to EPR Properties",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Six Flags Entertainment (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FUN\" title=\"Six Flags Entertainment Corporation\">FUN</a></span></span>) has sold seven parks to EPR Properties for $331M as part of the company’s efforts to optimize its portfolio and bolster its balance sheet.</p>\n<p>Included in the transaction are Valley Fair in Minnesota, Worlds of Fun in Kansas City, Michigan’s Adventure, the Schlitterbahn Waterpark in Galveston, Texas, Six Flags St. Louis, Six Flags Great Escape in Queensbury NY, and Six Flags La Ronde in Montreal. These parks all generate ~$260M in net revenue and ~$45M in adjusted EBITDA.</p>\n<p>The proceeds of the sale will be used to pay down debt. Last quarter, the company had $5.18B in long-term debt with cash and cash equivalents of $91M.</p>\n<p>“By focusing our resources on the parks that we believe have the highest growth potential, we expect to drive operating leverage, expand margins, and accelerate our cash flow generation,” said Six Flags Entertainment CEO John Reilly. <span> </span></p>\n<p>The decision to unload seven parks comes in the wake of disappointing fourth-quarter results in which the company fell further into the red with a loss of $0.91 per share. This largely reflected a 9% drop in Q4 admission revenue and a 13.3% drop in attendance. And while expenses were down, this was a result of fewer visitors to the parks and reductions in seasonal labor, some of which were offset by higher property taxes and higher wage costs.  </p>\n<p>Over the past year, shares of Six Flags Entertainment (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FUN\" title=\"Six Flags Entertainment Corporation\">FUN</a>) have consistently underperformed the S&amp;P 500, lagging the benchmark index by 76 percentage points.</p>\n<p>Shares are down 2% in Thursday's premarket trading. </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4561263-six-flags-entertainment-shedding-seven-parks-to-epr-properties",
            "pub_date": "2026-03-05 22:15:24",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
